<h4 class="header"><i>2.1.17</i>Question 17<a class="headerlink" href="#question-17_2" name="question-17_2">&para;</a></h4>
<p>What is a limit? Seriously, how do you prove shit</p>
<h4 class="header"><i>2.1.18</i>Question 18<a class="headerlink" href="#question-18_1" name="question-18_1">&para;</a></h4>
<p>sigh</p>
<h3 class="header"><i>2.2</i>Section 3.2<a class="headerlink" href="#section-32" name="section-32">&para;</a></h3>
<h4 class="header"><i>2.2.1</i>Question 1<a class="headerlink" href="#question-1_6" name="question-1_6">&para;</a></h4>
<blockquote>
<p>Converge/diverge?<br />
(a) <span>$x_n = n/(n+1)$</span><br />
(b) <span>$x_n = (-1)^nn/(n+1)$</span><br />
(c) <span>$x_n = n^2/(n+1)$</span><br />
(d) <span>$x_n = (2n^2+ 3)/(n^2+1)$</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p>(a) Converges to 1. Proof: ?</p>
<p>(b) I think it diverges. Proof: ?</p>
<p>(c) Diverges. Proof: ?</p>
<p>(d) Converges to 2. Proof: ?</p>
<h4 class="header"><i>2.2.2</i>Question 2<a class="headerlink" href="#question-2_6" name="question-2_6">&para;</a></h4>
